<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-21T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">423.11 L 23/329: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-21T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">June 21,
                                        1921—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 22—9:25
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>50. Department’s 33, June 20, 4 p.m. Peruvian Government has appointed
                            Señor Carlos Prevost Commissioner in Landreau arbitration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>